			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000060_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><date when="1857-04-07"><p rend="right">7<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> April </p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857 </p></date>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir </p>
<lb/><p>I went at once 
<lb/>after your call this 
<lb/>morning to the 
<lb/><persName>Lord Mayor</persName>, and 
<lb/><choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> a cheque 
<lb/>for Â£200. I stated 
<lb/>my wish distinctly 
<lb/>that I want the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000060_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'-->
<lb/>money paid over 
<lb/>to <persName>Messers Coutts &amp; Co-</persName>
<lb/>the Bankers. For 
<lb/>this a committee 
<lb/>must be again 
<lb/>called so in 
<lb/>order to make 
<lb/>the matter plain 
<lb/>I have now 
<lb/>written the <persName>Lord 
<lb/>Mayor</persName> to the same effect. At the 
<lb/>last meeting they 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000060_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/>wished to ascertain 
<lb/>my wishes respecting 
<lb/>the disposal of 
<lb/>the money. I have 
<lb/>said, then my 
<lb/>wishes are that 
<lb/>it be paid to 
<lb/>my account at 
<lb/>the Bankers - 
<lb/>there can be no 
<lb/>mistake now. </p>
<lb/><p>I shall write also to <persName>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Tidman</persName> to 
<lb/>the same effect<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_000060_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'-->
<lb/>I called at Coutts to ask 
<lb/>them to <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> it. 
<lb/>And they are quite agreeable 
<lb/>to do so. </p>
<lb/><p>I now beg you 
<lb/>will accept my 
<lb/>heartfelt thanks 
<lb/>for the kind interest 
<lb/>you have manifested 
<lb/>in the matter </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">And am </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Your much obliged </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
